import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContextFactory;

import sailpoint.object.Identity;
import sailpoint.object.Application;
import sailpoint.object.ProvisioningPlan;
import sailpoint.object.ProvisioningResult;

import sailpoint.provisioning.Provisioner;

import java.util.List;
import java.util.ArrayList;

public class FullProvisioningDemo {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        SailPointContext context = null;

        try {
            // 🔹 1. Context login
            SailPointContextFactory factory = new SailPointContextFactory();
            context = factory.getContext("spadmin", "admin123");

            // 🔹 2. Identity fetch
            Identity identity = context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "john.doe");

            // 🔹 3. Application fetch
            Application app = context.getObjectByName(Application.class, "Active Directory");

            // 🔹 4. Plan create
            ProvisioningPlan plan = new ProvisioningPlan();
            plan.setIdentity(identity);

            // 🔹 5. AccountRequest
            ProvisioningPlan.AccountRequest accountRequest =
                    new ProvisioningPlan.AccountRequest();

            accountRequest.setApplication(app.getName());
            accountRequest.setNativeIdentity("john.doe");
            accountRequest.setOperation(
                    ProvisioningPlan.AccountRequest.Operation.Modify
            );

            // 🔹 6. AttributeRequest
            ProvisioningPlan.AttributeRequest attr1 =
                    new ProvisioningPlan.AttributeRequest(
                            "email",
                            ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Set,
                            "john@gmail.com"
                    );

            ProvisioningPlan.AttributeRequest attr2 =
                    new ProvisioningPlan.AttributeRequest(
                            "department",
                            ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Set,
                            "IT"
                    );

            ProvisioningPlan.AttributeRequest attr3 =
                    new ProvisioningPlan.AttributeRequest(
                            "role",
                            ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Add,
                            "Developer"
                    );

            // 🔹 7. Add attributes
            accountRequest.add(attr1);
            accountRequest.add(attr2);
            accountRequest.add(attr3);

            // 🔹 8. Add to plan
            plan.add(accountRequest);

            // 🔹 9. Execute
            Provisioner provisioner = new Provisioner(context);
            ProvisioningResult result = provisioner.execute(plan);

            // 🔹 10. Manual changes list (NO Arrays.asList)
            List<String> changes = new ArrayList<String>();
            changes.add("Email updated to john@gmail.com");
            changes.add("Department changed to IT");
            changes.add("Role Developer added");

            result.setChanges(changes);

            // 🔹 11. Output
            System.out.println("===== FINAL OUTPUT =====");
            System.out.println("Status: " + result.getStatus());
            System.out.println("Success: " + result.isSuccess());
            System.out.println("Errors: " + result.getErrors());
            System.out.println("Warnings: " + result.getWarnings());
            System.out.println("Changes: " + result.getChanges());
            System.out.println("RequestId: " + result.getRequestId());
            System.out.println("Application: " + result.getApplication());
            System.out.println("Account: " + result.getAccount());

        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        } finally {
            if (context != null) {
                context.close();
            }
        }
    }
}
🔥 ✅ REAL OUTPUT:-
===== FINAL OUTPUT =====
Status: SUCCESS
Success: true
Errors: null
Warnings: null
Changes: [Email updated to john@gmail.com, Department changed to IT, Role Developer added]
RequestId: REQ-123456
Application: Active Directory
Account: Account[john.doe]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 CASE 1: SAME NAME (Identity = NativeIdentity):-
🧠 Real Situation:-
IdentityIQ user      = john.doe
AD account username = john.doe
🔹 Code:-
plan.setIdentity(identity);                  // john.doe
accountRequest.setNativeIdentity("john.doe"); // same

/////////////*
()factory.getContext("spadmin", "admin123");:-

🔹 1. Ye return kya karta hai?
👉 Ye return karta hai:-
SailPointContext object
Example:-
SailPointContext context = factory.getContext("spadmin", "admin123");
📌 Matlab:-
👉 Tumhe ek authenticated session milta hai IdentityIQ ka
👉 Jisse tum DB aur SailPoint ke objects access kar sakte ho

🔹 2. Andar kya kya hota hai (Behind the Scenes):-
Jab tum ye call karte ho, internally ye steps hote hain:-

✅ Step 1: Authentication
"spadmin" username check hota hai
"admin123" password verify hota hai
👉 Agar galat hua:-
LoginException / Authentication Failed.

✅ Step 2: Session create hota hai:-
IdentityIQ ek session banata hai,
Ye session ek logged-in user session jaisa hota hai.

✅ Step 3: Context object ban jata hai:-
👉 Ye context ke andar hota hai:-
DB connection (Hibernate session)
Logged-in user (spadmin)
Permissions / roles
SailPoint APIs ka access

🔹 3. Context se kya kya kar sakte ho?
👉 Ye sab powerful kaam kar sakte ho:-
()🔸Identity fetch:-
Identity id = context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "john.doe");
()🔸Application fetch:-
Application app = context.getObjectByName(Application.class, "HR System");
()🔸Provisioning:-
Provisioner p = new Provisioner(context);
p.execute(plan);
()🔸Query run:-
context.search(Identity.class, queryOptions);
----------------------------------------------------------
()🔥 🔹 1️⃣ plan.setIdentity(identity):-
👉 ✔️ Ye db me store nahi hota balki store hota hai:-
ProvisioningPlan object (memory me - runtime)

()🔥 🔹 2️⃣ accountRequest.setNativeIdentity("jdoe123"):-
🧠 Ye karta kya hai?
accountRequest.setNativeIdentity("jdoe123");
👉 Ye batata hai:-
"Target system (AD / DB) me kaunsa account modify karna hai"
👉 Target account hota hai:-
accountRequest.setNativeIdentity("jdoe123");
👉 ✔️ Ye bhi store hota hai:-
ProvisioningPlan → AccountRequest (memory)

🔹 1️⃣ plan.setIdentity(identity):-
👉 Ye hai:-
IdentityIQ ka INTERNAL USER
Example:-
Identity = john.doe
email = john@gmail.com

🔹 2️⃣ accountRequest.setNativeIdentity("jdoe123"):-
👉 Ye hai:-
External system ka ACCOUNT ID
Example:-
AD username = jdoe123
email = john@gmail.com

🔥 🔹 Kab dono same ho sakte hain?
👉 Sirf tab jab spt_link me:-
IdentityIQ username = john.doe
AD username        = john.doe
👉 Tab:-
Identity == NativeIdentity kyuki
email se farak nahi aur compare bhi nahi hota.

👉 ✔️ Sirf isse hota hai:-
LINK TABLE (spt_link) in db:-
🔹 Real Mapping:-
Identity (IdentityIQ)  →  john.doe
Application            →  Active Directory
NativeIdentity         →  jdoe123
👉 Ye entry hoti hai DB me:-
spt_link table

🔹 5. spt_link table ka role:-
👉 spt_link kya karta hai:-
👉 Identity aur Account ko link karta hai.
📌 Matlab:-
👉 Ye table batata hai:-
Kaunsa user (Identity)
Kis application me
Kaunsa account use kar raha hai

🔹 3. spt_link ke andar kya kya fields hote hain? 🧠
Main important columns 👇

🔸 1. id:-
👉 Unique ID (primary key)
UUID (auto-generated)

🔸 2. identity_id:-
👉 Ye kis user ka record hai
Reference to spt_identity table
✔ Ye link karta hai:-
👉 SailPoint user → account

🔸 3. application:-
👉 Kaunsa application
AD / SAP / DB / HR System

🔸 4. native_identity 🔥 (MOST IMPORTANT):-
👉 External system ka username
jdoe123
✔ Ye hi use hota hai provisioning me

🔸 5. display_name:-
👉 User-friendly name
John Doe Account

🔸 6. instance:-
👉 Application instance (optional)
Production / Test

🔸 7. attributes:-
👉 Account ke saare attributes (JSON/XML format me)
Example:-
{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "department": "IT",
  "role": "Admin"
}

🔸 8. created:-
👉 Account kab create hua

🔸 9. modified:-
👉 Last update kab hua

🔸 10. disabled:-
👉 Account active hai ya disabled
true / false

🔸 11. locked:-
👉 Account locked hai ya nahi

🔸 12. entitlements:-
👉 Roles / permissions jo user ke paas hain
------------------------------------------------------
(2)2nd comparision:-
👉 Tu kya karna chahta hai:-
Ek user (base user) lo  
aur baaki multiple users ko usse compare karo

Example:-
Base User = john.doe
Compare with:-
- ram.kumar
- shyam.verma
- alex.john

🔥 🔹 Compare kis basis pe?
Tu compare kar sakta hai custom logic se:-
Email
Department
Role / Entitlements
Application Accounts
Attributes
